The paper presents a method for fabricating 3D models using multi-directional 3D printing systems, which involves developing an algorithm to minimize the usage of support structures. This involves addressing issues related to volume decomposition, collision-free fabrication, and generating special supporting structures. The paper also presents two different hardware systems to verify the effectiveness of the proposed method. Given these aspects, the paper is likely to belong to the following arXiv CS sub-categories: 

- cs.GR (Graphics): The paper deals with 3D printing and fabrication of models, which involves aspects related to computer graphics. 
- cs.RO (Robotics): The paper involves developing an algorithm for multi-directional 3D printing, which can be seen as a robotics problem. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The paper involves generating supporting structures for 3D printing, which can be seen as a computer vision problem. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper deals with 3D printing and fabrication of models, which can be seen as a multimedia application. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper involves developing an algorithm for volume decomposition, which can be seen as a machine learning problem.
